'''Şefik Yılmaz Dizdar''' (born 1938) is a Turkish [[billionaire]] businessman, one of the owners of LC Waikiki, a Turkish producer and retailer of clothing and homewares, with 700 stores in 34 countries, and annual sales of over $2 billion.<ref name="forbes1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/economy/2017/03/22/gates-worlds-richest-person-29-turks-constitute-461b-on-forbes-list |title=Gates world's richest person, 29 Turks constitute $46.1B on Forbes list |publisher=Daily Sabah |date=31 January 2017 |accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.turkishamericannews.com/business-news/item/7745-turkey-s-richest-people-revealed |title=Turkey’s Richest People Revealed |publisher=Turkishamericannews.com |date=29 February 2016 |accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref>
His brother [[Vahap Kucuk]], is the CEO and spokesman of LC Waikiki.<ref name="forbes1"/>
Dizdar is married, and lives in [[Istanbul]], Turkey.<ref name="forbes1"/>
